{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17487349","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17487349"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T03:07:04+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T03:07:04+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"327"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"327","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/327"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.02,0.14,0.61,0.19]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"327"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"90519"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"327","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/327"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"327"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"74759"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"35"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"390"},{"type":"tags","id":"1094"},{"type":"tags","id":"1144"},{"type":"tags","id":"1181"},{"type":"tags","id":"2163"},{"type":"tags","id":"3549"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"6612"},{"type":"tags","id":"8088"},{"type":"tags","id":"8218"},{"type":"tags","id":"8224"},{"type":"tags","id":"9423"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"946"},{"type":"contributions","id":"31048"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42059"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44751"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44919"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"90519","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/90519"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 76-year-old woman presents with a two month history of a rapidly enlarging lump in her neck (image). This enlargement has been painless. Over the last week she has experienced hoarseness and difficulty in swallowing. She has had an unintentional weight loss of 7 kg over the last three months. Her medical history includes a goitre (never investigated or treated) and gastro-oesophageal reflux disease. She has a 30 pack-year smoking history.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Carcinoma of the bronchus","Haemorrhage into a colloid cyst","Carcinoma of the larynx","Carcinoma of the thyroid","Carcinoma of the oesophagus"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe clinical picture suggests a malignant process to explain the rapidly growing lump in her throat. The fact that it is affecting her voice and swallowing also suggests a sinister cause.\u00a0The patient has a goitre within which malignant change can occur. Of the various options provided, this is the most likely underlying cause of her current problem. The fast growth of the tumour suggests it could be a rare \u003Cstrong\u003Eanaplastic thyroid cancer\u003C/strong\u003E, but this will not be confirmed until a biopsy is taken.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe patient has few risk factors for laryngeal cancer besides smoking, and this would generally present with other symptoms such as a chronic cough, haemoptysis and pain on swallowing. The lump is also unlikely to be so pronounced without these other symptoms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt is possible that the lump could represent metastatic disease e.g. thyroid cancer or SCC, or a lymphoproliferative disorder, but cervical node enlargement is not usually so pronounced, and malignant lymphadenopathy rarely if ever causes dysphonia. A haemorrhagic process might produce such a swelling, but would be associated with pain. The most appropriate management of this woman at this stage would be to do an ultrasound guided FNA to further investigate.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf the underlying problem was a carcinoma of the oesophagus, the patient\u0027s difficulties with swallowing would have gone back much longer than one week.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A rapidly enlarged neck mass and hoarseness suggests malignancy."],"references":["Cancer Council NSW, (2020).\u00a0Thyroid cancer\u00a0(online). Accessed at:\u00a0https://www.cancer.org.au/about-cancer/types-of-cancer/oesophageal-cancer.html.","Cancer Council, (2019).\u00a0Oesophageal cancer\u00a0(online). Accessed at:\u00a0https://www.cancer.org.au/about-cancer/types-of-cancer/oesophageal-cancer.html.","Cleveland Clinic, (2017).\u00a0Laryngeal Cancer Care Path\u00a0(online). Accessed at:\u00a0https://my.clevelandclinic.org/health/treatments/16611-laryngeal-cancer-care-path."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"74759"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"327"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"15180"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"15180","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/15180"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/c3078756-ab92-4c30-b1ac-8c9ad774cb30.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/c3078756-ab92-4c30-b1ac-8c9ad774cb30.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":554,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"74759","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/74759"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-14T09:53:07+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-14T09:53:07+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"327"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"90519"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"}